  "chapter": {
    "number": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Imitators of God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Be imitators of God, therefore, as beloved children,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "and walk in love, just as Christ loved us",
          {
            "noteId": 1565
          },
          "and gave Himself up for us as a fragrant sacrificial offering to God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "But among you, as is proper among the saints, there must not be even a hint of sexual immorality, or of any kind of impurity, or of greed."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "Nor should there be obscenity, foolish talk, or crude joking, which are out of character, but rather thanksgiving."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "For of this you can be sure: No immoral, impure, or greedy person (that is, an idolater), has any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "Let no one deceive you with empty words, for because of such things the wrath of God is coming on the sons of disobedience."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "Therefore do not be partakers with them."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Children of Light"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "For you were once darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Walk as children of light,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "for the fruit of the light consists in all goodness, righteousness, and truth."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "Test and prove what pleases the Lord."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "Have no fellowship with the fruitless deeds of darkness, but rather expose them."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "For it is shameful even to mention what the disobedient do in secret."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "But everything exposed by the light becomes visible,",
          {
            "noteId": 1566
          },
          "for everything that is illuminated becomes a light itself."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "So it is said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Wake up, O sleeper,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rise up from the dead,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and Christ will shine on you.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "Pay careful attention, then, to how you walk, not as unwise but as wise,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "redeeming the time, because the days are evil."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "Therefore do not be foolish, but understand what the Lord’s will is."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "Do not get drunk on wine, which leads to reckless indiscretion. Instead, be filled with the Spirit."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "Speak to one another with psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs. Sing and make music in your hearts to the Lord,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "always giving thanks to God the Father for everything in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Wives and Husbands"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "Submit to one another out of reverence for Christ.",
          {
            "noteId": 1567
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "Wives, submit to your husbands as to the Lord."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          "For the husband is the head of the wife as Christ is the head of the church, His body, of which He is the Savior."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          "Now as the church submits to Christ, so also wives should submit to their husbands in everything."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          "Husbands, love your wives, just as Christ loved the church and gave Himself up for her"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          "to sanctify her, cleansing her by the washing with water through the word,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          "and to present her to Himself as a glorious church, without stain or wrinkle or any such blemish, but holy and blameless."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          "In the same way, husbands ought to love their wives as their own bodies. He who loves his wife loves himself."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          "Indeed, no one ever hated his own body, but he nourishes and cherishes it, just as Christ does the church."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          "For we are members of His body.",
          {
            "noteId": 1568
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          "“For this reason a man will leave his father and mother and be united to his wife, and the two will become one flesh.”",
          {
            "noteId": 1569
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          "This mystery is profound, but I am speaking about Christ and the church."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          "Nevertheless, each one of you also must love his wife as he loves himself, and the wife must respect her husband."
        ]
      }
    ],
